name: Bristles - The Road Home
description:
This piece summarises the Bristles series. A photo of the house where I grew up in Western Australia, decades after leaving the city and the house had been sold. The road home ends in a place which is virtually unrecognisable save for the basic bones of the structure.

Original photography filtered through the lens of generative abstraction. Digital oil painted onto a noisy geometric canvas. 6000x6000. Made in Processing.
